==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Letterpress
<hw>Let"ter*press`</hw> <pr>(-t⟦etil⟧r*pr⟦ecr⟧s`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>Print; letters and words impressed on paper or other material by
types; -- often used of the reading matter in distinction from the
illustrations.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Letterpress printing, printing directly from type, in distinction
from printing from plates.</q>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Letterure</ent>⟦br⟧
